33,34,41,37,68,19,41,48]} 1. e4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. Nc3 Bg4 4. h3 Bxf3 5. Qxf3 e6
6. Be2 Nf6 {This is the most common move in the position. The knight is
directly fighting for control over the centre.} 7. O-O Bc5 {Black stops us
from playing the move d4 but at the same time, the bishop is more vulnerable
here. If we can go d4 we gain a full tempo.} (7... d4 {We saw very similar
lines in the previous chapters.} 8. Nb1 Nbd7 (8... Bd6 9. d3 Bc7 {This is the
top choice of computers and the usual plan of g3, Qg2 is not as effective here.
