{[%evp 0,15,68,24,39,42,12,-1,-2,-6,-7,-28,-10,-14,3,3,5,-34] Can we do
something creative here?} 7. a4 $1 $146 {This has never been played even
though there were more than 1100 games in the database. What is the point? We
stop Black's idea of going for the move c5 immediately by preparing the move
Bb5. It also allows us to go for Ba3 in the future. Another point is that
Qa5-a4 ideas are no longer possible.} O-O (7... Nxc3 8. bxc3 c5 9. Bb5+ $16) (
7... c5 8. Bb5+ Nc6 9. dxc5 $16) 8. Bd3 {Now the plan of Nxc3 and c5 is not as
effective as we can just develop normally. c4 and Qa5 can even be met with Qd2
followed by Ba3. Having the pawn on a4 helps us here. This is very similar to
my recommendation in the database against the French.} Nxc3 9. bxc3 c5 10. O-O
c4 11. Be2 f6 {Black has to try and create some counterplay.} 12. Re1 Nc6 13.
exf6 exf6 14. Nh2 {[%cal Ge2f3,Ga1b1,Gc1a3,Gh2g4,Gg4e3] We have easy play here
and several different ideas. The d5 pawn is a long-term issue for Black.} *

