{[%evp 0,15,46,32,33,40,40,40,44,43,40,48,50,35,35,29,29,-3] I recommend an
interesting concept here. What is it?} 9. Nd2 $5 {We have more space and I
like to preserve the minor pieces on the board. This is the general rule- the
side with space advantage should not trade minor pieces. This is because with
less space those minor pieces get cramped and lack the freedom to move around.}
Be7 10. O-O O-O 11. Rd1 {The rook is well placed here as we are expecting
Black to go for a pawn break with either c5 or e5.} a5 (11... Qc7 12. Nc4 {
We want to go for Bf4 next.} Nd5 13. Ne3 Rad8 14. c3 Rfe8 15. Bd3 h6 16. Nxd5
cxd5 17. g3 {We have a slight edge with the bishop pair.}) (11... Qa5 12. Nc4
Qd5 13. Qb3 Nb6 {1-0 (21) Vachier Lagrave,M (2780)-Ducarmon,Q (2479) Chess.com
INT 2019} 14. Ne5 Qxb3 15. axb3 $16 {White is quite a bit better, especially
with this pawn structure on the queenside.}) (11... e5 $5 12. dxe5 Nxe5 13. Qg3
Bd6 14. Nf3 Nxf3+ 15. Qxf3 Qe7 16. Bd3 $14 {The pawn structure is symmetrical
but we undeniably have a small edge with the pair of bishops.}) 12. a4 Nb6 13.
c3 Qd5 14. Qg3 (14. Qd3 Rfd8 15. Nf3 $14 {1/2-1/2 (30) Sindarov,J (2587)-Cori,
J (2655) Riga 2021}) 14... Qd6 15. Qxd6 Bxd6 16. Kf1 $14 {We have a very
pleasant endgame ahead of us.} *

