{[%evp 0,7,64,-19,56,38,72,50,67,52] How to continue with White?} 9. g4 $5 {
This has been played only twice but I like this idea of putting maximum
pressure on Black. I have analysed a lot of different options here and I did
not find any clear way to equalise.} Ne8 {Once Black removes his knight from
f6 we can build up our center.} (9... dxe4 {This happened in one of the games.}
10. dxe4 Nfd7 11. Qg2 e5 12. g5 $14 {White got a nice edge in the game 1/2-1/2
(68) Moussard,J (2632)-Suleymanli,A (2541) Riga 2021.}) (9... a5 {Is one of
the top choices of the computer but it does not achieve much.} 10. Qg3 {
[%cal Gf2f4]} (10. Qg2) 10... a4 11. a3 Ne8 12. f4 f5 13. Bf3 $14) (9... Nbd7
10. Qg2 {We want to go f4 next and it makes a lot of sense once Black has
already committed his other knight to d7.} d4 11. Nb1 e5 12. f4 $14) (9... Kh8
10. h4 {[%cal Gg4g5]} (10. Qg3 {1-0 (41) Malicka,M (2275)-Panek,B (2152)
Krakow 2023}) 10... Nbd7 11. g5 Ne8 12. Qh3 $14 {[%cal Gf2f4]}) 10. d4 a5 11.
a3 Nd7 12. Bd3 $14 {[%cal Gc1f4]} *

