{[%evp 0,13,53,42,46,37,37,34,30,39,47,50,55,48,47,36] Does Black have any
ideas here?} 12. Qe3 $1 {We stop the plan of Bg5.} (12. Bf4 $5 {Now Bf5 is no
longer effective and we also have control over the h2-b8 diagonal.} Nf6 (12...
Re8 13. Qf3 Nf8 14. Qb3 Ng6 15. Be3 Rb8 16. a4 $14) 13. Qf3 Nd5 14. Bd2 Bg5 15.
Be1 $14 {[%cal Ga2a4,Gc2c3,Gg2g3,Gh3h4] We get the typical middlegame with the
bishop pair.}) 12... Nf6 (12... Qc7 {Now Bg5 is no longer an issue.} 13. Qf3
Nf6 14. c3 a5 15. g3 $14) 13. Bf3 Qc7 14. Qe2 Rfd8 15. g3 {The usual rule in
these positions is to put pawns in the colour of the opponent's bishop to
restrict it. This will help us dominate the other colour.} Rd7 16. c3 a5 17.
Kg2 Rad8 18. Be3 $14 *

