{[%evp 0,9,67,57,54,54,60,49,51,62,62,51] Shall we defend the pawn with a3?} 
13. b5 $1 {We need to play dynamically here. We are preparing to go Nd4 next.}
cxb5 (13... Bg6 $1 {A good prophylactic move. We have two different ways to
pose problems here.} 14. Nh4 (14. a4 $5 a5 $1 {A very important move for Black
as he needs to stop our play on the queenside. Now things are not that easy
for us.} (14... Be7 15. a5 $14) 15. d4 c5 $1 {Again this is necessary to fight
back against our center. Otherwise, we would have gone for the move c5
ourselves.} 16. Bb2 f6 $11) 14... cxb5 15. cxb5 Bb4 $1 {Black has to keep an
eye on the d2 pawn.} (15... Be7 16. Nxg6 hxg6 17. Bb2 Bf6 18. Bxf6 Nxf6 19.
Rac1 $14 {[%cal Ge2f3]}) 16. a4 Bc2 {[%csl Gc2]} 17. Nf3 Rc8 18. a5 {[%cal
Gc1b2] White still has some initiative and Black has to defend accurately.})
14. Nd4 $1 {This is the point behind the move b5.} Bg6 (14... bxc4 15. Nxf5
exf5 16. Bxc4 $14) 15. Nxb5 Kd8 16. d4 a6 17. Nc3 $14 {And I got a nice edge
which I converted after a lot of difficulties in the game 1-0 (46) Arjun, K 
(2503) -Vaishali, R (2393) Barcelona 2021.} *

