{[%evp 0,15,47,14,39,31,41,41,41,43,43,42,44,43,49,47,46,27] Where to go with
the queen?} 9. Qd2 $1 {A strange square but we want to meet Bf5 with Bd3.} Bf5
{Black wants to go e6 and complete his development next.} (9... g6 {again
leads to comfortable play after} 10. Bc4 Bg7 11. O-O O-O 12. Re1 $14) 10. Bd3 {
This does usually favour the side with less space but does have some benefits
too. It enables us to finish development faster and get better control over
the centre.} Bxd3 11. Qxd3 e6 12. O-O Bd6 13. c4 {I think this is the only way
to keep posing problems for Black.} Ne7 14. Bd2 {The bishop will be perfect on
c3 keeping an eye on d4 and hinting at going d5 at the right moment.} O-O 15.
Qe4 Qd7 16. a4 $14 {A very typical move gaining space on the queenside. White
has a slight edge.} *

