{[%evp 0,21,35,-52,-26,-89,-79,-39,-50,-39,-50,-41,-47,-98,-65,-65,-81,-126,
-65,-70,-64,-51,-33,33] Do we have enough for the pawn?} 12. Ng5 $1 {We have
to play dynamically to prove our compensation.} Ne5 13. Rxe5 {All of the next
few moves are forced for Black.} Qxe5 14. Bxf7+ Kd8 15. Bc4 Ke8 16. h3 {
Clearing the back rank and preparing to get our other pieces into the game.}
Bf5 (16... Qe1+ 17. Kh2 Qe5+ 18. f4 $14) 17. d3 Qe1+ 18. Kh2 e6 19. g4 Qe5+ 20.
Kg1 Bg6 21. Nxe6 Kd7 22. Bf4 $36 {The position is quite complex but it is
clear that we are the ones with the initiative and Black has to be careful.} *

