{[%evp 0,27,32,61,62,38,65,62,53,16,55,39,29,38,81,0,54,55,44,46,20,-14,64,36,
30,33,38,55,49,51] [#]} {How to defend the c2 pawn?} 11. b3 $1 {The pawn on c2
is not really hanging here. We want to go Bb2 and 0-0-0 next.} Nd7 (11... a5 {
is too slow} 12. Bb2 h6 13. O-O-O a4 14. Nd4 Bc8 15. f4 (15. Rde1 axb3 16. axb3
$14 {Vachier Lagrave,M (2795)-Salem,A (2633) Moscow 2017}) 15... Na6 16. Rde1
$16 {None of Black's pieces are properly developed while we are looking to
start our initiative with f5 and g4.}) 12. Bb2 e6 (12... Nf6 13. O-O-O O-O-O $2
14. Ne5 Be6 15. Bc4 $18 (15. f4 {1-0 (129) Grabinsky, A (2350)-Zhai, M (2365)
Chess. com INT 2019})) (12... O-O-O $2 {is a big mistake due to} 13. Ng5 Bg6
14. Bh5 $18) (12... e5 13. O-O-O Bd6 14. d4 e4 15. Nh4 Be6 16. d5 $1 {A very
nice idea to open up the position and win one of the bishops.} cxd5 17. Nf5 $1
Bxf5 18. Rxd5 $16) 13. O-O-O h6 14. Rde1 {Black is still not able to castle
easily. We have ideas of Nh4 and Bh5 exploiting the king on e8.} Rg8 (14...
O-O-O $2 {unfortunately fails to} 15. Ng5 $1 Bg6 16. Bd3 $18) (14... Bh7 15. g4
$16) (14... Nf6 15. Ne5 Rd8 16. g4 Bh7 {1/2-1/2 (67) Bharath, S (2495)-Aronyak,
G (2519) chess24.com INT 2022} 17. Nc4 $16 {We want to go f4 and g5 next.}) 15.
Nh4 (15. Nd4 $5 {is another decent alternative.} Bg6 16. g4 {We want to get f5
very quickly.} O-O-O 17. f4 Bd6 18. f5 exf5 19. gxf5 Bh7 20. Bh5 Rdf8 21. a4
Nf6 22. Bf3 Re8 23. Rxe8+ Rxe8 24. g4 $14) 15... Bh7 16. Bh5 Ke7 {An
unfortunate necessity for Black.} 17. f4 $146 {We do not slow down. There are
other interesting ideas but this is the most direct.} g5 $1 {It is important
for Black to create some counterplay.} (17... g6 18. Bg4 $16 {[%cal Gh4f3,
Gf3e5]}) 18. fxg5 Rxg5 19. g4 Bg7 20. Ba3+ c5 21. Nf3 Rd5 {The rook is very
unstable but there is no way to trap it.} 22. g5 hxg5 23. Bxf7 Kxf7 24. Rxh7
$14 {White has a lot of pressure in this endgame. Black has to play very
accurately to defend.} *

