{[%evp 0,11,87,14,60,66,42,38,48,19,21,28,17,19] Can you find the top choice
of the computer here?} 15. Bd2 $1 $146 {A typical computer move. White is
preparing to go Nd6 and Bb4. He does not mind giving up the d4 pawn for long
term compensation.} (15. c3 f5 16. Nc5 $1 Nxc5 17. dxc5 {We are playing
against Black's light-squared bishop.} Bd7 18. Be3 O-O-O 19. O-O-O $14 {
One idea is to double on the 'd' file with Rd6. We can go f4 next and fix the
weakness on e6.}) 15... Bxd4 (15... a5 16. g4 $14) 16. O-O-O {We have a lot of
activity to compensate for the missing pawn.} Bg7 17. g4 b6 18. g5 hxg5 19.
Rxh8+ Bxh8 20. Bxg5 $14 {[%cal Ge4d6] Black is unable to finish his
development. We can go f4, g4 and f5 if given the chance. Bb7 will always be
met with Nd6.} *

